Cognitive Work Plane (CWP)
Documentation Master Plan (Aligned to NS-GGP Canonical Template)
PurposeThis document defines the authoritative documentation master plan for the Cognitive Work Plane (CWP), strictly aligned to the existing NS-GGP document structure (000–014).
CWP is the agentic HR, operations, and management plane for Northfield Solidarity. It is responsible for representing, coordinating, and supervising agentic workers (human, AI, and hybrid), operational tasks, roles, responsibilities, and performance — while remaining fully governed by GGP.
CWP is not:
A governance authority (GGP)
A financial system (FLO)
A pure execution engine (DAT)
CWP is the operational cognition layer that translates intent into coordinated work.

CWP Documentation Index (Canonical)

NS-CWP-000 — CHARTER
Purpose: Define why CWP exists
Scope:
Mission of CWP
Why agentic work coordination must be centralized
CWP’s role as the operational nervous system
Explicit non-goals (policy governance, accounting, market execution)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-000

NS-CWP-001 — OVERVIEW
Purpose: High-level conceptual framing
Scope:
What CWP manages (agents, roles, tasks, workflows)
Relationship to human operators and AI agents
Interaction with core engines (GGP, DAT, PTE)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-001

NS-CWP-002 — TAXONOMY
Purpose: Define CWP’s atomic work concepts
Scope:
Agent (human / AI / hybrid)
